  <h2>1. The service</h2>
  <p>TaxVett provides an API for validating tax identification numbers (EU VAT numbers, UK tax numbers, Australian ABNs, Norwegian organisation numbers, and Singapore tax IDs) and related developer tooling including documentation, SDKs, and a usage dashboard.</p>

  <h2>2. Accounts</h2>
  <p>You must provide a valid email address to create an account. You are responsible for keeping your API key confidential. If you suspect your key has been compromised, regenerate it immediately from your dashboard. You may not share your API key with third parties or use it to build a competing tax validation API.</p>
  <p>You must be at least 18 years old (or the age of legal majority in your jurisdiction) to use TaxVett.</p>

  <h2>3. Plans and rate limits</h2>
  <p>TaxVett offers the following plans. Rate limits are enforced using a sliding-window algorithm and excess requests receive a <code>429 Too Many Requests</code> response.</p>

  <table>
    <tr><th>Plan</th><th>Requests / day</th><th>Requests / minute</th><th>Batch size</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Free</td><td>100</td><td>10</td><td>Up to 10</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Pro</td><td>10,000</td><td>60</td><td>Up to 50</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Enterprise</td><td>Unlimited</td><td>300</td><td>Up to 50</td></tr>
  </table>

  <p>We reserve the right to adjust rate limits with reasonable notice to maintain service quality for all users.</p>

  <h2>4. Payment and billing</h2>
  <p>Paid plans (Pro, Enterprise) are billed monthly through Stripe. Prices are shown at checkout and may include applicable taxes. Subscriptions auto-renew unless cancelled. You may cancel at any time from your dashboard; cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period.</p>
  <p>All payments are processed by Stripe, Inc. By subscribing to a paid plan you also agree to <a href="https://stripe.com/legal" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stripe's Terms of Service</a>. TaxVett does not store your full payment card details.</p>
  <p>We do not offer refunds except where required by applicable law.</p>

  <h2>5. Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You may use TaxVett to validate tax numbers in your own products and services. The following uses are prohibited:</p>
  <ul>
